quran[82]{c,v,t}:
  100,9,Does he not know that when the contents of the graves are taken out and examined
  100,10,And that which was in (human) minds recovered
  100,11,"Their Lord shall have been well-aware of them, that Day"
  101,1,The Sudden Calamity
  101,2,What is the Sudden Calamity
  101,3,And what do you know what the Sudden Calamity is
  101,4,It is a Day when mankind shall be like the scattered moths
  101,5,And the mountains like fluffed up wool
  101,6,"That person, then, who weighs heavy [with good deeds] on the scales"
  101,7,"[That person] shall have a pleasant life"
  101,8,"And that person, who weighs light [because of bad deeds] on the scales"
  101,9,The Abyss then shall be his home
  101,10,"And what do you understand what it [the Abyss] is"
  101,11,A Fire intensely hot
  102,1,"The craving for more [worldly wealth and power] keeps you engrossed"
  102,2,Until you embrace the graves
  102,3,Nay! You shall soon come to know
  102,4,Nay again! You shall soon come to know
  102,5,"Nay, if you but knew with certain knowledge"
  102,6,You shall surely see the Hell
  102,7,Then you shall surely see it with eye of certitude
  102,8,"And then, on that Day, you shall surely be questioned about the bounties you enjoyed"
  103,1,By the time
  103,2,"Indeed, mankind is surely in loss"
  103,3,"But not those among them who believe and do good deeds, and exhort one another to Truth, and exhort one another to patience"
  104,1,"Woe to everyone who taunts, slanders, or backbites others"
  104,2,"Who hoards wealth and keeps on counting it [avariciously]"
  104,3,Thinking his wealth will last forever for him
  104,4,Nay! He will surely be thrown into the Crushing Disaster
  104,5,And what do you know what the Crushing Disaster is
  104,6,It is the Fire kindled by Allah
  104,7,That which would ride over human minds
  104,8,It would be closing in on them from everyside
  104,9,In extended columns
  105,1,Have you not seen what your Lord did to the companions of the elephant
  105,2,Did He not bring their plan to naught
  105,3,And send upon them swarms of birds
  105,4,Pelting them with stones of baked clay
  105,5,And then making them look like chewed husk?h
  106,1,For the welfare of the Qurays
  106,2,"Their welfare during winter and summer journeys [of their trading caravans]"
  106,3,So let them worship the Lord of this House
  106,4,Who provided them food against hunger and security against fear
  107,1,Have you seen the one who denies that there is a just divine system in place for mankind
  107,2,Such a one it is that pushes the orphan away
  107,3,And does not motivate others on feeding the poor
  107,4,"And, woe to those who pray —"
  107,5,"Those who are neglectful of, and/or inattentive in, their Prayers"
  107,6,Those who show off
  107,7,And refuse to give even trifling things to others
  108,1,We have indeed given you the amplitude
  108,2,So pray to your Lord and offer sacrifice for Him
  108,3,Your enemy is the one to be cut off
  109,1,"Say, \"O you who suppress the Truth"
  109,2,I worship not that which you worship
  109,3,And you worship not Him Whom I worship
  109,4,And I shall worship not that which you worship
  109,5,And you worship not Him Whom I worship
  109,6,"For you your way of life and for me, mine"
  110,1,When Allah's help and the victory have come
  110,2,"And you see people entering Allah-ordained way of life for mankind, in large numbers"
  110,3,"Then glorify your Lord with His praise, and seek His forgiveness. HE is indeed the One to accept repentance"
  111,1,Abu Lahab's hands are perished; and he too
  111,2,His wealth and what he earned was of no avail to him
  111,3,"[In the life to come] he shall burn in a Fire of blazing flames"
  111,4,"Along with his wife, carrier of (thorny) wood —"
  111,5,A rope of twisted strands in her neck
  112,1,"Say, \"He is Allah, the One and Only"
  112,2,"Allah, the eternal and independent Lord and Master on Whom everything in the Universe depends"
  112,3,He begets not nor is He begotten
  112,4,And there is none comparable to Him
  113,1,"Say, \"I seek refuge in Lord of the dawn"
  113,2,From the evil of what He has created
  113,3,And from the evil of darkness when it sets in
  113,4,And from the evil of those who blow on knots
  113,5,And from the evil of the envious person when he envies
  114,1,"Say, \"I seek refuge in the Lord of mankind"
  114,2,King of mankind
  114,3,One Whom mankind should worship
  114,4,"From the evil of the temptations, doubts and suggestions of the stealthy whisperer"
  114,5,— One who puts the evil things in minds of mankind —
  114,6,From among the jinn and mankind